<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7399> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7399" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proq(uaestor) under Cn. Pompeius Magnus (32) in Spain (see MRR 2.298, and Crawford, RRC 1.480, no. 470, 46-45 B.C.). Probably the M. Minatius M. f. Porn. Sabinus who supervised the building of a tower and wall at Casilinum (not Tegianum) in Lucania (CIL 1(2).2.1686-ILS 5321-ILLRP 395). See V. Bracco, MAL 1962, 432, note 9; Wiseman, NM 241, no. 256.\n" .
